1.Task: Launch an EC2 instance on AWS
Manual Steps:

Login to AWS Console

Select AMI, instance type

Configure networking, key pair, etc.

Launch instance

Ansible Automation (Example):
# launch-ec2.yml
- name: Launch EC2 instance in AWS
  hosts: localhost
  gather_facts: no
  tasks:
    - name: Launch EC2
      amazon.aws.ec2_instance:
        name: test-server
        key_name: my-key
        instance_type: t2.micro
        image_id: ami-0abcdef1234567890
        region: us-east-1
        count: 1
        wait: yes





âœ… OS Patching Automation
 Task 2: Apply security updates on all Linux servers
Manual Steps:

SSH into each server

Run yum update or apt-get upgrade

Ansible Automation (Example):
 patch-linux.yml
- name: Patch all Linux servers
  hosts: all
  become: true
  tasks:
    - name: Update all packages (CentOS/RHEL)
      yum:
        name: '*'
        state: latest
      when: ansible_os_family == "RedHat"

    - name: Update all packages (Ubuntu/Debian)
      apt:
        upgrade: dist
        update_cache: yes
      when: ansible_os_family == "Debian"






âœ… Log Rotation Automation
ðŸ”¹ Task 3: Rotate custom application logs
Manual Steps:

Create a logrotate configuration file

Test log rotation

Ansible Automation (Example):

- name: Setup log rotation
  hosts: all
  become: true
  tasks:
    - name: Create logrotate config for myapp
      copy:
        dest: /etc/logrotate.d/myapp
        content: |
          /var/log/myapp/*.log {
              daily
              rotate 7
              compress
              missingok
              notifempty
              create 0640 root root
          }



âœ… User Creation and Permission Setup
ðŸ”¹ Task 4: Add a new developer user with sudo access
Manual Steps:

Add user manually

Set password

Modify sudoers

Ansible Automation (Example


- name: Add developer user
  hosts: all
  become: true
  tasks:
    - name: Create user
      user:
        name: devuser
        password: "{{ 'MySecurePassword' | password_hash('sha512') }}"
        shell: /bin/bash

    - name: Add to sudoers
      lineinfile:
        path: /etc/sudoers
        line: 'devuser ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL'
        validate: '/usr/sbin/visudo -cf %s'






5. âœ… Service Monitoring/Restart
ðŸ”¹ Task 5: Check and restart a crashed service (e.g., nginx)
Ansible Automation (Example):

- name: Ensure nginx is running
  hosts: web
  become: true
  tasks:
    - name: Start nginx if not running
      service:
        name: nginx
        state: started
        enabled: true
